	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />To get a 1 pixel brush in Gimp 2.8, I click pencil, then I click on the brush shape (big square in the &quot;tool options&quot; pane), for me the second brush was a little dot, it's called &quot;1. Pixel&quot;. Finally there is a &quot;size&quot; field just below, change that to 1.00, and you should be able to draw hard pixels.<br /><br />I also recomend going to preferences &gt; tool options, and telling it to save the tool options on exit so you don't have to do this every time.<br /><br />For other tools like the eraser, some of them have individual options for anti-aliasing or hard edges. Eraser has a &quot;hard edge&quot; option you want to turn on, for example.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


